bug.message: A method should have only one exit point, and that should be the last statement in the method.
Found non-transient, non-static member. Please mark as transient or provide accessors.
Avoid modifiers which are implied by the context.
System.exit() should not be used in J2EE/JEE apps.
Each class should declare at least one constructor.
Use explicit scoping instead of the default package private level.
It is a good practice to call super() in a constructor.
Rather than using a lot of String arguments, consider using a container object for those values.
Avoid using Literals in Conditional Statements.
Avoid unused method parameters such as 'ethFilter'.
Avoid unnecessary constructors - the compiler will generate these for you.
Avoid unused private methods such as 'generateFixedTypes(MethodSpec.Builder,String)'.
These nested if statements could be combined.
Avoid unused private fields such as 'thisObj'.
Use one line for each declaration, it enhances code readability.
Assigning an Object to null is a code smell. Consider refactoring.
If you run in Java5 or newer and have concurrent access, you should use the ConcurrentHashMap implementation.
Avoid unused private methods such as 'generateFixedTypes(Class,String)'.
Use of modifier volatile is not recommended.
